The paper focuses on sentiment and emotion semantics in social multimedia, which suggests it could belong to the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), multimedia (cs.MM), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The development of a multilingual visual sentiment concept ontology involves computer vision techniques, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of language-specific models, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
